#META# documentSubtype: Legal: Sale
#META# writingSupport: paper
#META# writingSupportDetails: fold lines :: pasted into Mirza Khwaja Muhammad’s notebook :: tears
#META# writingSupportNotes: Incomplete (top part missing), black ink. In the top and bottom right corner are notes written by Mirza Khwaja Muhammad in ball point pen
#META# foldLinesCount: 5
#META# foldLinesAlignment: horizontal
#META# contentSummary: Legal query (*istiftā*) addressed to religious authorities regarding whether a seller of land can challenge the validity of the annulment (*iqālat*) of a sale with a representative (*wakīl*) acting on behalf of his nephew (*khwāhar-zāda*). The annulment met the following conditions: 1) the seller was mature and of sound mind; 2) it was conducted voluntarily; 3) the payment was received from the representative; 4) the nephew did not object. The response, authored by ʿUmar b. Muḥammad, denies the seller 's claim.
